author: The Associated Press
title: LI high school computer system hacked
text:
LI high school computer system hacked The Associated Press Order Reprint of this Story COMMACK, N.Y. 
Authorities say a Long Island high school's computer system containing class schedule and student identification data has been hacked. 
The Commack school district said in a statement on its website that an unauthorized person breached the system Thursday night. But it says there was no evidence that any specific student information was downloaded. 
Newsday (http://nwsdy.li/1Mgi8wW ) reports that the district believes the breach applies to a very limited number of high school student records. 
Suffolk County police say they have a suspect but did not release additional information. Related content
